    "jays": {
      "full_name": "Toronto Blue Jays",
      "league": "MLB",
      "record": "7-9",
      "detail": "4th in AL East",
      "live_strip": null,
      "lotl": {
        "label": "What's Going On With the Jays",
        "body": "Vladimir Guerrero Jr. ripped a go-ahead RBI double in the 10th, igniting the Toronto Blue Jays' <strong>thrilling 9-7 extra-innings escape over the Brewers</strong> last night &mdash; a gritty road win that snapped their skid and breathed life into a middling start. At 7-9, they're clinging to fourth in the AL East, three games back, with a fragile one-game win streak after dropping two straight to the Twins. Vladdy's clutch heroics &mdash; that sharp liner to left flipping a 6-7 deficit &mdash; masked a bullpen that coughed up a three-run homer earlier, but the bats outlasted Milwaukee's young stud Jacob Misiorowski in an insane back-and-forth. No fresh injuries piling on, though the rotation's thin amid whispers of opportunity. This bunch isn't contending yet, but yesterday's fire hints at traction if they harness it. <strong>Tonight's rubber match at 6:40 PM ET sends Dylan Cease to the hill against the Brewers</strong> &mdash; snag a series win, and the East chase sharpens; flop, and it's back to the pack.",
        "updated": "Updated April 15, 2026"
      },
