        "body": "The draft smoke thickens over Washington, where a 5-12 stumble left the Commanders clinging to third in the NFC East, nine games back and eyeing salvation at pick seven. <strong>Yesterday's buzz lit up Commanders Wire: a top-30 visit with controversial wideout Jordyn Tyson</strong>, the Arizona State firebrand whose off-field shadows make him a no-go at seven but a Day 2 temptation if he slides. GM Adam Peters, fresh off inking safety Nick Cross in free agency, preaches patience around Jayden Daniels&mdash;whose legs carried 800 yards last fall&mdash;but the roster screams for elite tackle or corner help, with mocks from Kiper floating edge rushers like Bain or versatile backs. Whispers of trades swirl too: slide back for volume or lunge up for a QB successor like Arkansas' Taylen Green on Day 3, hedging Marcus Mariota's exit. No panic yet&mdash;Peters built depth at safety with Cross and Harris&mdash;but this war room hungers for speed opposite Daniels' spark. <strong>With the Pittsburgh draft 10 days out April 23, watch if Tyson clears character hurdles or forces a bold swap&mdash;roster rebirth hangs on it.</strong>",
